Talent Management Software Overview | TrustRadiusAre You a Tech Marketer?HomeTalent Management SoftwareTalent Management SoftwareFollowing Follow CategoryOverviewListingsReviewsArticlesBuyer's GuideOverviewListingsReviewsArticlesBuyer's GuideFollowing Follow CategoryBest Talent Management SoftwareTrustMaps are two-dimensional charts that compare products and services based on end-user satisfaction ratings and research
frequency by prospective buyers. You can filter the data by company size, because small businesses and enterprises can have very different needs.Products and services must have 10 or more ratings to appear on the TrustMap,
and those above the median line are considered Top Rated.  Top Rated Talent Management Software include: UltiPro, RedCarpet, Workday HCM, Oracle HCM, Cornerstone OnDemand, PeopleFluent Mirror Suite for Talent Management, Kenexa, Saba, and Cornerstone Growth Edition.Other Talent Management Software on the TrustMap include: SuccessFactors Talent Solutions, SelectSuite, PeopleMatter, Lumesse, and HRSmart.A complete list of Talent Management Software is available here.Talent Management Software OverviewWhat is Talent Management?Talent management is sometimes considered a synonym for performance management. However, in reality, talent management software is a set of HR capabilities—including but not limited to performance management—that are considered strategically important to the organization. One possible definition is that talent management software is designed to manage talent through the entire lifecycle from talent acquisition through development to reward and measurement, in order to ensure that the best people are being hired, developed and trained and compensated to maximize value for the organization.Talent Management SolutionsThe primary constituent elements of talent management suites form a continuum of activities and processes, revolving around the most important resource in any organization--its people. The primordial talent concerns of most organizations include:Talent acquisition, especially improving the quality of hiresSpeeding up the time to competencyImproving performance and developmentMaking sure that everyone is working on projects with the highest potential for impactEnsuring that talent is rewarded and compensatedFinding a new generation of leadersContinuously developing staff to meet the fast changing needs of the modern corporationA talent management system is designed specifically to help organizations solve common HR pain points and meet these highly strategic goals.Talent Management Software Features & CapabilitiesThe various talent management components are as follows: Recruitment/ATS Recruiting, or talent acquisition, is considered a key component of talent management. These features may be delivered as a module within a talent management suite, or through integration with a standalone recruiting/ATS tool. Typical recruitment features include:Job requisition managementCompany website postingSocial media publishingJob search site postingCustomizable application formsResume managementDuplicate candidate preventionCandidate searchApplicant trackingCollaborationTask creation and delegationEmail templates for communication with candidatesUser permissionsNotifications and alerts, particularly for interviewsStandard reports on key recruiting metrics such as time-to-fillOnboardingEmployee onboarding is the process or orienting new hires to the social and performance aspects of their jobs so that they are able to function in their new roles as quickly as possible. Talent management features to help with onboarding often include:New hire portalManager tracking toolsCompliance tracking and reportingPerformance Management & Compensation ManagementPerformance management is the process of ensuring employees meet pre-determined objectives and goals through regular check-ins and appraisals. Compensation management involves determining employee pay grades (salary, bonuses, commission, etc.) based on performance metrics. Features around performance and compensation management are:Performance plans and performance improvement plansPlan weighingManager note takingReview status tracking, review reminders, and review transferMultiple review frequencyRater nominations and rater nomination workflowWorkflow restrictionsReportingGoal AlignmentTalent management solutions often have features that help to measure and improve performance in relation to specific business goals. Goal alignment is the practice of ensuring that all employees have clearly defined goals in support of the overall corporate strategy. The term "cascading goal alignment" refers to the synchronization of goals at different levels. These features support goal alignment:Corporate, subordinate, and individual goal settingNon-hierarchal goal settingLine-of-sight-visibilityPerformance trackingSuccession Planning & Learning ManagementSuccession planning is the identification and development of internal employees with the potential to fill key business leadership positions in the company. Learning management is the process of planning and assisting with employee training in new skills, often to prepare employees for new and/or higher level positions; standalone learning management systems are available. Internal succession is often dependent on successful learning management. Features in this area allow users to:Create succession plans/poolsRank candidatesManage and update employee profilesSearch for candidatesAdd new candidatesAssign learning and development goals to candidatesTalent Management Listings Listings   All Types   ListingsSearchListings (1-25 of 91)Sort by: Reviews | Highest Rated | Lowest Rated | Alphabetical | Product | Service(591) 8.3UltiProUltimate Software delivers cloud-based HCM solutions that help businesses accelerate talent acquisition, simplify payroll computations, manage time and attendance, and support proactive, strategic talent management.Reviews (462)AlternativesUltiPro Product Tour(327) 7.0ADP Workforce NowADP Workforce Now is an cloud-based HR platform for mid-sized businesses.Reviews (160)AlternativesCompare ADP Workforce Now(228) 7.5Oracle HCM CloudOracle HCM aims to go beyond the basics of HR. According to the vendor, an attractive UI, social, mobile, and reporting capabilities are now table stakes of every HR solution. Oracle HCM aims to allow its users to become strategic leaders of talent, by being engaging, informative, and...Reviews (74)AlternativesVisit Website(108) 7.3Cornerstone OnDemandCornerstone OnDemand is a cloud-based application for talent management.  The company's solut